This file explains how setting various environment variables will
affect the running of ExOS:

HEAP_ZERO - the heap will be zeroed
NO_HEAP_DEMAND_ALLOC - all the memory for the heap will be allocated during
			 the call to brk
NO_HEAP_SOFT - by default, ExOS will not immediate deallocate all unused memory
			when the breakpoint is decremented.  This option will
			makes sure all unused memory is deallocated.
NO_DEMAND_LOAD - by default, programs linked to use the shared library will
			be demand loaded
